# Related Datasets and Research Resources

## Overview

The **Turkish Delight Corpus (TDC)** is part of a broader ecosystem of open datasets, software tools, and computational resources developed for Turkish makam music research.

While this book primarily focuses on the computational analysis of **SymbTr v3.0**, several complementary datasets have been developed by the Music Technology Group (MTG), Universitat Pompeu Fabra (UPF), to support research on phrase segmentation, melodic analysis, symbolic music processing, and music information retrieval (MIR).

This chapter provides an overview of these resources together with representative research studies that have contributed to the development of computational methods for Turkish makam music.